riations across the burst\ndomain. Our results suggest a scenario where simultaneous and co-spatial EBs\nand UV bursts are part of the same reconnection system occurring sequentially\nalong a vertical or nearly vertical current sheet. Heating and bidirectional\njets trace the location where reconnection takes place. These results support\nand expand those obtained from recent numerical simulations of magnetic flux\nemergence.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Wed, 23 Oct 2019 18:00:10 GMT"}],"update_date":"2020-01-15"}
