 $\\Gamma$ at the QCP for each class even though characteristic\nenergy scale of spin fluctuation $T_0$ is finite at the QCP, which gives a\nfinite contribution in $\\Gamma_a=-\\frac{V}{T_0}\\left(\\frac{\\partial\nT_0}{\\partial V}\\right)_{T=0}$. General properties of $\\alpha$ and $\\Gamma$\nincluding their signs as well as the relation to $T_0$ and the Kondo\ntemperature in temperature-pressure phase diagrams of Ce- and Yb-based heavy\nelectron systems are discussed.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Thu, 24 Oct 2019 07:31:05 GMT"}],"update_date":"2019-10-25"}
