lpha}$, $\\alpha\\in (0,2)$, where $c$ is a positive constant. Our main\nresult in this part is a boundary Harnack principle which says that, for any\n$p>(\\alpha-1)_+$, there are values of the parameters $\\beta_1, \\beta_2,\n\\beta_3$, $\\beta_4$, and the constant $c$ such that non-negative harmonic\nfunctions of the process must decay at the rate $x_d^p$ if they vanish near a\nportion of the boundary. We further show that there are values of the\nparameters $\\beta_1, \\beta_2, \\beta_3$, $\\beta_4$, for which the boundary\nHarnack principle fails despite the fact that Carleson's estimate is valid.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Thu, 24 Oct 2019 07:52:41 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Wed, 7 Oct 2020 11:06:44 GMT"},{"version":"v3","created":"Wed, 4 Aug 2021 14:12:55 GMT"},{"version":"v4","created":"Mon, 5 Dec 2022 00:45:13 GMT"}],"update_date":"2022-12-06"}
