ndes-Rousses massif.\nSubstantial Pearson R^{2} correlations (0.75-0.90) of MODIS observations with\nsimulations are found over the domain. This suggests that assimilating it could\nhave an impact on the spatialized snowpack forecasting system. However,\nobservations contain significant biases (0.1-0.2 in reflectance) which prevent\ntheir direct assimilation. MODIS spectral band ratios seem to be much less\nbiased.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Thu, 24 Oct 2019 08:01:22 GMT"}],"update_date":"2019-10-25"}
